  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Cut your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into wedges, leaving the skin on (this helps them cook quicker)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1585753996717-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1585753996717-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1585753996717-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1585753996717-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1585753996717-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong>, <strong>onion wedges</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> (skins on) to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Add your <strong>dried oregano</strong> with a large drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 5 min or until the tomatoes are beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1585754000817-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1585754000817-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1585754000817-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1585754000817-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1585754000817-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, roughly tear your <strong>basil</strong>, including the stalks</p><p>Add the <strong>torn basil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> and bash for 1-2 min or until it looks like a purée (alternatively, pulse in a<strong> </strong>food processor)</p><p>Add 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and<strong> half</strong> your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) then stir to combine – this is your<strong> balsamic basil purée</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
