    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[380ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>in a pot<strong> </strong>and add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Once the tomatoes have caramelised, remove the tray[s] from the oven and carefully cut the roots from the <strong>onion wedges</strong></p><p>Carefully remove the skins from the <strong>onion</strong> and <strong>garlic </strong>and discard (beware, they will be hot!)</p>",
